    "pre_narrative": "### **MISSION BRIEFING: THE STANDOFF**\n\n**DATE:** December 29, 2025  \n**LOCATION:** Supreme Court of Nova Scotia  \n**CASE:** *R. v. Francis*\n\nThe province is in a state of high tension. [cite_start]On December 4, 2025, the Justice Minister directed a massive crackdown on 'unauthorized' cannabis dispensaries, citing public safety concerns regarding mould and crime links[cite: 111, 118]. [cite_start]The RCMP raided **Leo’s Trading Post** on the Millbrook First Nation, but the community responded with a **Sacred Fire** and blockade, asserting that provincial law has no power on unceded territory[cite: 65, 66].\n\n**YOUR JOB:** You are a senior clerk for the Chief Justice. [cite_start]You must navigate a complex web of 18th-century promises and modern international standards like UNDRIP[cite: 13, 14]. [cite_start]Does the Treaty of 1752 give Leo the right to sell 'any other thing'—including cannabis—without a provincial license?[cite: 18, 25]. Review the evidence. [cite_start]Apply the Marshall and Sparrow tests[cite: 43, 45]. Decide the law.",
