        "primary": {
          [cite_start]"body": "## **THE SACRED FIRE**\n\nOn December 4, the RCMP arrived to execute a provincial warrant[cite: 111]. [cite_start]They were met by a **Sacred Fire** lit in the shop's doorway[cite: 65]. [cite_start]In Mi'kmaw culture, this fire is a spiritual boundary; stepping over it is a profound desecration[cite: 65, 66]. [cite_start]\n\nBeside the fire, the community hung **Red Dresses** to symbolize Missing and Murdered Indigenous Women[cite: 65]. [cite_start]The message was clear: 'You prioritize raiding our businesses over finding our missing daughters'[cite: 65, 66]. [cite_start]The raid was no longer just about cannabis; it was a PR disaster for the Crown, highlighting the deep divide between provincial policing and Indigenous survival[cite: 112, 113].",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/rcmp-protest-ai.jpg",
          "credit": "AI"
        },
        "legal": {
          [cite_start]"body": "## **BAND COUNCIL RESOLUTION (BCR)**\n\nLeo didn't just open a shop; he opened a shop authorized by **Indigenous Law**[cite: 112]. [cite_start]The Millbrook Chief and Council passed a **BCR** stating they alone regulate cannabis on their land[cite: 112, 125]. \n\nThis creates a 'Conflict of Laws.' [cite_start]The Province has its *Cannabis Control Act*, but the Band has its inherent right to self-government[cite: 30, 35]. [cite_start]Under **UNDRIP Article 3**, the Band has the right to manage its own economic systems[cite: 85, 102]. [cite_start]The question for the court is which law wins: the Provincial rule or the Indigenous Law?[cite: 35, 125].",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/band-door-AI.jpg",
          "credit": "AI"
        },
        "intel": {
          [cite_start]"body": "## **THE LAB ANALYSIS**\n\nThe Crown's only excuse for the raid is **Public Safety**[cite: 31, 111]. [cite_start]They claim unregulated cannabis is laced with mould or fentanyl[cite: 31, 111]. [cite_start]However, Exhibit C is a **Lab Report** from an independent clinic[cite: 6]. [cite_start]\n\n**Findings:** Pesticides (None), Mould (None), THC (Accurate)[cite: 6]. [cite_start]This evidence 'explodes' the Crown's narrative[cite: 40, 41]. [cite_start]If the product is safe and clean, the raid wasn't about protecting the public—it was about protecting the Province's **Tax Monopoly**[cite: 29, 31]. [cite_start]This makes the raid an 'unjustified infringement' of Leo's rights[cite: 45, 89].",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/leo-test-report.jpg",
          "credit": "AI"
        }
      }
