      "shortTitle": "The Crown",
      "longTitle": "EXHIBIT D: The Minister's Warning",
      "interactionPrompt": "FIELD ANALYSIS (Cite evidence): Review the Googoo Decision. Does this precedent kill Leo's case?",
      "options": ["Review Precedent"],
      "tabs": {
        "primary": {
          [cite_start]"body": "## **THE FLOODGATES ARGUMENT**\n\nNova Scotia's Justice Minister warns the court of 'chaos'[cite: 111, 118]. [cite_start]He argues that if Leo wins, the province will be flooded with 118+ unregulated shops[cite: 111]. [cite_start]'We cannot have a country with two sets of laws,' he says[cite: 30, 31]. [cite_start]\n\nThe Minister insists that **Reconciliation** does not mean a 'legal vacuum' where anyone can sell anything[cite: 11, 31]. [cite_start]He argues that the Province's **Fiduciary Duty** (legal obligation) is to protect everyone—Indigenous and non-Indigenous—from the dangers of an unregulated drug market[cite: 34, 77].",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/scott-armstrong-and-dr-strong-micmacrightsdotcom.jpg",
          "credit": "micmacrights.com"
        },
        "legal": {
          [cite_start]"body": "## **THE GOOGOO TRAP**\n\nThe Crown's strongest weapon is **R. v. Googoo (2024)**[cite: 11, 50]. [cite_start]In that case, the judge ruled that because the Mi'kmaq didn't trade cannabis in 1752, they have no right to trade it today[cite: 49, 56]. [cite_start]\n\nThis is the **'Frozen Rights'** approach[cite: 22]. [cite_start]The Crown argues that Treaty rights are only for 'traditional' activities like trapping beavers[cite: 22, 33]. [cite_start]Leo's lawyer must prove that cannabis is a modern version of those old goods[cite: 25, 26]. [cite_start]If the court follows *Googoo*, Leo's case is finished[cite: 57, 121].",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/googoo-ai.jpg",
          "credit": "AI"
        },
        "intel": {
          [cite_start]"body": "## **THE EMPTY BOX**\n\nThe **Empty Box Theory** is the foundation of the Crown's power[cite: 32, 33]. [cite_start]They argue that until Leo proves his right in court, the 'box' of Section 35 is empty, and the Province's *Cannabis Control Act* fills the void[cite: 33, 35]. [cite_start]\n\nHowever, intelligence reports show that on December 9, First Nations began banning cabinet ministers from their lands in response to this 'empty' view of their rights[cite: 112, 126]. [cite_start]The 'Empty Box' is no longer just a legal theory; it is a political fuse that has reignited the fire of Indigenous resistance across the province[cite: 112, 113].",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/magicbox-1-ai.jpg",
          "credit": "AI"
        }
