          [cite_start]"body": "## **THE FINAL PEN STROKE**\n\nThe Judge is waiting for your memo[cite: 16]. [cite_start]This decision will decide the future of Indigenous business in Canada[cite: 11, 114]. [cite_start]\n\nIf you rule for Leo, you are telling the Province they must treat First Nations as **Equal Governments**, not just subjects[cite: 89, 97]. [cite_start]If you rule for the Crown, you are confirming that the Province has the 'Final Say' on what happens on reserve land[cite: 35, 91]. [cite_start]The ink is still wet on the **UNDA Progress Report (2025)**, which says Canada must align all laws with Indigenous rights—but the Province is clearly fighting back[cite: 82, 83].",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/judgement-1-ai.jpg",
          "credit": "AI"
        },
        "legal": {
          [cite_start]"body": "## **THE UNBALANCED SCALES**\n\nJustice is symbolized by scales, but for Leo, the scales are weighted against him by the **Indian Act** and the **Cannabis Control Act**[cite: 35, 73]. [cite_start]\n\nTo balance them, Leo uses the **Eagle Feather of Truth** and Section 35[cite: 8, 17]. [cite_start]He argues that the 'Law of the Land' (the Treaty) is higher than the 'Law of the Province'[cite: 25, 29]. [cite_start]Under the **Marshall Standard**, the Crown must prove its law is 'minimal'[cite: 46]. [cite_start]If they can't prove that Leo's shop specifically harmed someone, then their 'Safety' weight is lighter than the Treaty's weight[cite: 41, 47].",
          "image": "http://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/leo-sitroom2/images/feather.jpg",
          "credit": "AI"
        },
        "intel": {
          [cite_start]"body": "## **THE HANDSHAKE (UNDRIP)**\n\nIntelligence shows a path to peace: **Economic Reconciliation**[cite: 82, 97]. [cite_start]**UNDRIP Article 20** says Indigenous peoples have the right to maintain their own economic systems[cite: 85, 104]. [cite_start]\n\nInstead of raids, the Crown could have formed a 'Joint Safety Board' with the Mi'kmaq[cite: 89, 98]. [cite_start]This would respect the **Honour of the Crown** and satisfy **FPIC**[cite: 75, 87]. [cite_start]By choosing the raid instead of the handshake, the Province ignored the 2025 AFN progress reports calling for co-developed policies[cite: 83, 99]. [cite_start]Your decision will either push the government toward this handshake or lock them in a cycle of conflict[cite: 11, 114].",
